<h2 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-Goals">Goals</h2>
<h3 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-Backgroundandstrategicfit">Bac=
kground and strategic fit</h3>
<ul>
<li>TCP output is available in RATs only in Velocity on Enterprise.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-Assumptions">Assumptions</h3>
<h3 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-Questions">Questions</h3>
<h3 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-TestingResources">Testing Reso=
urces</h3>
<p>To test TCP output, you can run a python script like the one below and u=
se the IP and port numbers as the parameters to the TCP output in a RAT.</p=
>
<h4 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-PythonMethod">Python Method</h=
4>
<ul>
<li>Pre-requisite: have Python installed on the machine</li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeHeader panelHeader pdl hide-border-bottom" style=3D"borde=
r-bottom-width: 1px;">
<b class=3D"code-title">Expand for Python Script</b><span class=3D"collapse=
-source expand-control" style=3D"display:none;"><span class=3D"expand-contr=
ol-icon icon">&nbsp;</span><span class=3D"expand-control-text">Expand sourc=
e</span></span><span class=3D"collapse-spinner-wrapper"></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl hide-toolbar">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: py; gutter: true; theme: Confluence; collapse: true" data-theme=3D"Conflu=
ence">import socket

HOST =3D '127.0.0.1'  # Localhost
PORT =3D 5578         # Port to listen on

server_socket =3D socket.socket(socket.AF_INET, socket.SOCK_STREAM)
server_socket.bind((HOST, PORT))
server_socket.listen(1)

print(f"Server listening on {HOST}:{PORT}...", flush=3DTrue)

while True:
    client_socket, addr =3D server_socket.accept()
    print(f"Connection from {addr}", flush=3DTrue)

    while True:
        data =3D client_socket.recv(1024)
        if not data:
            print(f"Client {addr} disconnected.", flush=3DTrue)
            break
        print(f"Received: {data.decode(errors=3D'ignore')}", flush=3DTrue)

    client_socket.close()</pre>
</div>
</div>
<h2 id=3D"RATOutputTCPClient(EnterpriseOnly)-Requirements">Requirements</h2=
>
